HOUSE BILL No. 1278
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 25-23-1-20.1.
Synopsis: Nursing education programs. Allows an institution that has
been operating an eligible nursing program for at least five years to
increase the enrollment in any eligible nursing program at any rate the
institution considers appropriate.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Barrett
January 6, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Health.
